## Improvement conventions

- Every improvement is a Git commit with a clear message.
- Format: `<skill-name>: <what changed>` (e.g., `voice-author: add register mapping phase`)
- System changes: `voice: <what changed>`
- Profile changes: `config: <what changed>`

## Please family

voice-please is one of four please-family frameworks. When the work points beyond voice definition and encoding, reach for a sibling.

| Framework | What it does |
|-----------|-------------|
| [strategy-please](https://github.com/yesplease-studio/strategy-please) | Workshop recommendation engine — diagnoses strategic gaps and prescribes the right workshop to run |
| [prd-please](https://github.com/yesplease-studio/prd-please) | PRD methodology — translates strategy decisions into structured product specifications and executable tasks |
| [sales-please](https://github.com/yesplease-studio/sales-please) | Deal qualification — WORTH framework for deciding which deals deserve time |

### When to suggest a sibling

| Suggest | When |
|---------|------|
| **strategy-please** | Voice work surfaces positioning confusion. The company can't define its voice because it doesn't know what it stands for or who it's for. Voice is the symptom; strategy is the fix. |
| **prd-please** | Voice artifacts are complete and they need to be incorporated into a product spec — particularly for products with AI-generated content, onboarding copy, or language as a core feature. |
| **sales-please** | Voice artifacts exist and the user wants to operationalize them in outbound sequences, discovery scripts, or sales materials. |
